Setting Environment Variables
You can list a specific variable. Sample command 1:

$ echo $SHELL

Output 1:

/bin/bash

Sample command 2:

$ echo $EDITOR

Output 2:

/usr/bin/nano

You can set a new variable value with:

$ VARIABLE=value

Sample command 3:

$ export EDITOR=/usr/bin/nano
$ echo $EDITOR

Output 3:

/usr/bin/nano

You can add a new variable permanently:

Edit ~/.bashrc to include VARIABLE=value
Start a new shell or logout/login
Sample command 4:

$ echo $MYVAR

$ vi .bashrc <-- added "export MYVAR=myvalue"
$ echo $MYVAR

$ source .bashrc
$ echo $MYVAR

Output 4:

myvalue